## Core Objectives 
Create one Unified project launchpad called "Portal" which will achieved by calling the QX QSWAP & QIP smart contracts built on Qubic. the Idea is to create resources for startup project wishing to build within the Qubic eco system. THis stands to solve Several problems.
1. Community Voting and resulting in early validation for approved projects.
2. ICO mechanism allows for free and fair distributions of revenue, for project funding and LP initialization
3. Trusted environment for projects to drive community traction by providing resources for Marketing & development. 

## Portal User flow 
1. Connect wallet 
2. Project details form:
    - Project Name
    - SC 
        - Ticker
        - redistributions
            - % for SC Holders
            - additional allocations
    - Token 
        - ticker 
        - Tokenomics 
    - project team
        - founder(s)
        - operations
        - developer(s)
        - marketing
        - other
    - development type
        - Token
        - Smart Contract
        - Hybrid
    - project description
    - Estimated Fundraising Goal
    - Project Wallets
        - default wallet 
        - percentage
        - vesting period
        - staggered release percentages (i.e. 5% released each month of vesting period)
    - project links
        - github repo (required)
        - socials
        - website
        - discord 
    - Project initiation fee (200m)
3. Approve in wallet
4. Project Goes Live 
5. Community voting 
    - pay 1m Qubic to vote yes
    - pay 0 Qubic to vote no
    - voting closes after 1 epoch
    - funds are returned if projec gets declined
6. Approved token projects go to ICO phase
    - Voting fees are reapplied to QX Issuance fee (1b Qubic)
    - remaining Fee revenue then purchases supply of ICO @ phase one.
    - Acquired tokens are porportionally distributed to each participating wallet
    - ICO progresses through Phase 2 & 3. 
    - remaining tokens automatically get locked in LP
    - ICO revenue is split between Incubator fund & LP. 
7. Funds are distributed to Project team in phases based on benchmarks being met.
8. Once project development concludes then remaining funds are locked into the vesting phase where fund release is staggered to the percentage rate specicfied at signup
    - each release of funds, must be signed by default wallet
    - once Vesting period congludes The remainder of funds are released to the default wallet. 
    - tokens and funds that do not get approved for release by default wallet will automatically be locked into LP after 90 days of final release. 

